    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I am also not yet quite happy with it. Will see if I can strip this further and split into several commits, but I wanted to hear feedback before I dump another 1/2 weekend on it. So far I didn't hear destructive criticism only so I may drop the idea entirely.\n\n> I don't think it is reasonable for you to ask us to add nearly 30000 lines of code (thats 30% of the entire project!) and maintain an incompatible fork of our low-level platform integration to save 2MB in our binary packages.\n\nThe main reason is not really file size especially in these days, but runtime performance. We are already maintaining an incompatible dead-end fork at https://github.com/OpenRA/SDL2-CS/tree/openra This just makes it easier for downstream packagers to build it.\n"
  },
